<div class="article-headline" id="Headline">SPAGHETTI WITH MINI MEATBALLS AND PEPPERONI SAUCE</div>

<div class="article-byline" id="ByLine">BY JAMIE DEEN</div>

<div class="article-in-image" id="image1"><img src="images/page045.article002.image1.jpg" class="article-in-image" alt=""/></div>
<div id="separatorLine"> <div class="invisible">empty</div> </div>

<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY MAC JAMIESON</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes 6 to 8 servings </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1 pound lean ground beef </p><p class="no-indent">¼ cup Italian seasoned bread crumbs </p><p class="no-indent">1 large egg </p><p class="no-indent">1 teaspoon dried Italian seasoning </p><p class="no-indent">¾ teaspoon salt </p><p class="no-indent">2 tablespoons vegetable oil, divided </p><p class="no-indent">½ cup chopped onion </p><p class="no-indent">3 cloves garlic, minced </p><p class="no-indent">2 (14.5-ounce) cans diced tomatoes with basil, garlic, and oregano, undrained </p><p class="no-indent">2½ cups prepared marinara sauce </p><p class="no-indent">1 cup mini turkey pepperoni </p><p class="no-indent">1 (16-ounce) package spaghetti </p><p class="no-indent">Garnish: shredded Parmesan cheese, chopped fresh parsley </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. In a large bowl, gently combine beef and next 4 ingredients. Working with 2 teaspoons beef mixture at a time, form into about 36 mini meatballs. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. In a large Dutch oven, heat 1 tablespoon oil. Working in 2 or 3 batches, add meatballs and cook for about 4 minutes or until browned on all sides. Drain meatballs on paper towels. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">3. In Dutch oven, heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil. Add onion and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes or until onion is soft. Stir in tomatoes and marinara sauce, scraping browned bits from bottom of pan with a wooden spoon. Stir in pepperoni and meatballs. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat; reduce heat to medium, and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes or until meatballs are done. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">4. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over high heat. Add spaghetti and cook for 8 minutes or until tender; drain well. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">5. Serve meatball mixture over spaghetti. Garnish with cheese and parsley, if desired.</p></div>
